    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-22T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-22T23:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10632: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-23T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 23, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of November 22, 3 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d487fn23">Not
                        printed.</note> Cantonese authorities have just informed me aeroplanes will
                    bombard Wuchow in the next day or two. I have asked commander of U. S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Mindanao</hi>, now at Wuchow, to advise Americans to leave if
                    possible, but at the same time warned Cantonese authorities time is short and
                    many Americans may not be able to get away, that United States Government will
                    expect every precaution to be taken to avoid harm to Americans and their
                    property and that I could give no assurance as to our attitude in the event of
                    Americans being killed or property damaged. As Cantonese now have 10 or 12
                    planes, bombing may be serious.</p>
                <p>Legation and Department has been informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
